<body>
    <form action="/nandihills" method="get">
    <div id="nav">
          <p id="p1">Nandi Hills</p>
         <hr style="border-color:black;position:relative;top: 70px;">
         <div id="i1">
            <img id="apimg" src="https://img.traveltriangle.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Cover2.jpg">
        </div>
        <br><br><br><br><br>
        <div id="i2">
            <h2><strong><center>INFORMATION</center></strong></h2>
            <hr style="width: 950px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p>Nandi Hills, also known as Nandidurg or Nandi Betta, is a popular hill station located in the Chikkaballapur district of Karnataka, India. It is situated approximately 60 kilometers away from Bengaluru, the state capital. <br>

                Best Time to Visit- Throughout the year, but the ideal time is between November and May, as the weather remains pleasant during this period. <br>
                
                Ideal Vacation Duration- 1-2 days <br>
                
                Average expenses: Starting from ₹8,000 (2 days/1 night) <br>
                
                Places to Visit- Tipu's Drop, Nandi Temple, Amrita Sarovar, Yoga Nandeeshwara Temple, Muddenahalli, Nehru Nilaya, Bhoga Nandishwara Temple, Sultanpet, Brahmashram, Paragliding Point. <br>
                
                Things to Do- Watching the mesmerizing sunrise and sunset from the hilltop, trekking to the top of the hill, paragliding for breathtaking views, visiting historical sites related to Tipu Sultan, exploring the beautiful temples and gardens. <br>
                </p>
            
        </div>
        <div id="i3">
            <center><h2>WEATHER</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;">
            <div class="icon">
            <h1><%=temp%>°C</h1><img src="/day/default.png" alt="" srcset="" id="image">
            </div>
            <h1 class="climate"><%=climate%></h1>
                <h2>Humidity : <%=humidity%>%<br><br>Wind Speed : <%=windspeed%>kmph</h2>
        </div>
        <div id="i4">
            <center><h2>TRANSPORTATION</h2></center><br>
            <hr style="width: 360px;height: 1.5px;background-color: black;"><br>
            <p> <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=oOAYqE64W2MO&format=png" height="25px" width="25px" alt="">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Air- The nearest airport is Kempegowda International Airport in Bengaluru, which is about 60 kilometers away from Nandi Hills.<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=d8MqKVWJkyqN&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp; By Train-Nandi Hills does not have a railway station; the nearest major railway station is Bengaluru City .<br><br>
                <img src="https://img.icons8.com/?size=1x&id=f42OOoV1ACzO&format=png" alt="" height="25px" width="25px">&nbsp;&nbsp;By Road-Nandi Hills is well-connected by road. You can reach here by hiring a taxi or taking a bus from Bengaluru or other nearby towns.</p>
        </div>
    </form>
    <script>
        
